carbons and changes in formation pressure discrete fracture modeling of hydraulic stimulation in enhanced geothermal systems mark mcclure in enhanced geothermal systems egs hydraulic stimulation is carried out by injecting water at high pressure into low permeability typically crystalline rock in most cases the fluid injection causes slip on the preexisting fractures enhancing their permeability and increasing well productivity stanford energy resources engineering 367 panama street green earth sciences 065 stanford university stanford ca 94305 2220 phone 650 723 4744 fax 650 725 2099 2012 stanford university related resources hartley conference center health and safety computers resources room resources how can we help maps & directions stanfordwho office of the registrar contact us connect to earth sciences facebook itunes u twitter youtube
